[32:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your conversation so far. So, anything that you\'ve told to the agent, that\'s going to use up some tokens. Anything the agent has done, including looking up files or making code diffs, all of that is using tokens as well. And there\'s a maximum amount of tokens you can use'

[32:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'before the agent starts forgetting things. And model providers have put hard limits because of this fact. So, if you\'re using a model like Opus, for example, I think now we have a limit of a million tokens because they upped it'

[32:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'recently, but this just gives you the percentage of how close are you to that ceiling before it starts forgetting everything. And once it hits that ceiling, it\'s going to summarize the whole conversation so that the agent can'

[33:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'keep going. And that\'s something called compaction. If you ever want to go look that up in our docs, that\'s what happens when you run out of context. You compact everything that was going on into a nice summary so that the agent can keep going and have much fewer context tokens in'

[33:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'its window. Uh, I hope that makes sense at a high level. Really, it\'s just how close are you to the ceiling. If you\'re really close to the ceiling, you might want to start a new conversation or you might want to summarize this conversation into a doc to keep it going. It\'s a'

[33:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
